Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop @potatoes{3} lengthways into 1cm slices, then into 1cm chips (peeling optional).

On a lined #baking tray{}, toss with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Spread out in a single layer. When oven is hot, cook on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

When ~{5%minutes} of cooking time remain, push the chips together and scatter over the @grated cheese{50%grams}. Cook until melted.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press).

Mix the @gochujang paste{1%sachet} (use less if you don't like spice) and the @aioli{1%sachet}.

Pop the @breadcrumbs{1%pack} into a #medium bowl{} and season with salt and pepper.

In another medium bowl, mix @flour{1%tbsp} and @water{50%ml}. Season with salt and pepper. Mix together.

> Double flour and water amounts for 4p.

Lay the @Irish chicken breast{320%grams} out on a #cutting board{}. Place a hand on top.

Cut the chicken horizontally from thick end to thin point until there's 2cm left. Open it up like a book.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Dip the chicken first in flour, then breadcrumbs.

Once well coated, transfer to a #plate{}.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging used to keep it fresh.

Place a #large pan{} over high heat with enough @oil{to taste} to fully coat the bottom.

Once hot, carefully lay the crumbed chicken into the pan and fry until golden brown and cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Turn every ~{2-3%minutes} and adjust heat as necessary.

Once cooked, transfer the chicken to a clean plate lined with #kitchen paper{}. 

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.
> TIP: Allow the oil to get hot so the chicken can fry properly.

Drain the excess oil from the pan and return to medium-high heat.

Lay in the @Irish bacon{170%grams} and fry until crispy and brown, ~{3-4%minutes} on each side.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Add a knob of @butter{to taste}, @sugar{1/4%tsp} and garlic to the pan and allow to melt.

> Double sugar for 4p.

Baste the bacon in the butter, then remove the pan from the heat.

When everything is almost ready, pop the @brioche buns{2} into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once warmed, spread a spoonful of spicy aioli onto each bun base.

Top with the chicken and bacon.

Spoon some melted garlic butter from the pan over the cut side of the bun lids before sandwiching shut.

Divide the cheesy chips between plates.